abstract: We don’t think of the premiums we already pay as taxes, but maybe we should.
snippet: We don’t think of the premiums we already pay as taxes, but maybe we should.
lead_paragraph: As the national debate about health care kicks off ahead of the 2020 presidential election, we’re going to be hearing a lot about the costs of increasingly popular progressive proposals to provide universal health care, like Bernie Sanders’s Medicare for All plan.

abstract: Despite doubts about his candidacy, Joe Biden begins the race with substantial support from three key constituencies in his native state, a place the Democrats can’t afford to lose again.

lead_paragraph: PITTSBURGH — The case for Joseph R. Biden Jr. has always come down to Pennsylvania.

headline_main: In Pennsylvania, Joe Biden Finds Support Where He Most Needs It
headline_print_headline: Biden’s Appeal Taps the Voters His Party Needs

abstract: Four years ago, Barack Obama gently discouraged him from running for president, but Joseph R. Biden Jr. is back and presenting himself as Mr. Obama’s natural heir.
snippet: Four years ago, Barack Obama gently discouraged him from running for president, but Joseph R. Biden Jr. is back and presenting himself as Mr. Obama’s natural heir.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — Barack Obama did not think Joseph R. Biden Jr. should run for president — he hardly needed to say it out loud for aides to understand that. The trick that summer of 2015 was finding a way to nudge Mr. Biden to stay out of the race without looking as if he was nudging Mr. Biden to stay out of the race.

abstract: Thinly veiled rebukes of the White House Correspondents’ Dinner was a running theme of a campaign rally in Wisconsin, where the president also zeroed in on policy.
snippet: Thinly veiled rebukes of the White House Correspondents’ Dinner was a running theme of a campaign rally in Wisconsin, where the president also zeroed in on policy.
lead_paragraph: GREEN BAY, Wis. — The White House Correspondents’ Dinner meant so little to the Trump administration and its boosters that thinly veiled rebukes of the First Amendment-focused event were a running theme of the president’s Saturday night campaign rally in Wisconsin.

headline_main: Even Away From Correspondents’ Dinner, Trump Makes Sure to Have His Say
headline_print_headline: Trump Has Say Away From Reporters’ Event

abstract: Only in America is the word freighted with so much perceived menace.
snippet: Only in America is the word freighted with so much perceived menace.
lead_paragraph: To be trapped in the boarding area of a smallish airport in the upper Midwest is, as often as not, to be subjected to that bestial din of fricatives, gutturals, plosives and shrieks of hysterical alarm that constitutes political discussion on Fox News, pouring incessantly from those obnoxious pendulous ceiling televisions. And unless one fancies running the T.S.A.’s gantlet of gropers again, there’s no escape. The experience is especially nasty if one’s wait coincides with the prime-time shows hosted by those two almost indistinguishable fellows with the suety faces, bouffant coiffures and nerve-racking mezzo-castrato voices.

abstract: Mr. Sanders staked out a bold position on voting rights, touching off the latest policy debate of the Democratic presidential primary.
snippet: Mr. Sanders staked out a bold position on voting rights, touching off the latest policy debate of the Democratic presidential primary.
lead_paragraph: The question was stark: Would you support enfranchising incarcerated people like the Boston Marathon bomber or convicted rapists?

abstract: Mr. Sanders’s campaign kicked off its national organizing program Saturday with what it says are roughly 5,000 events across every state.
snippet: Mr. Sanders’s campaign kicked off its national organizing program Saturday with what it says are roughly 5,000 events across every state.
lead_paragraph: Just days after former Vice President Joseph R. Biden Jr. became the 20th candidate to join the Democratic presidential race, Senator Bernie Sanders of Vermont readied what he hoped would be his latest show of force: thousands of house parties across the country.
